<subSubSection id="C36F650CFFD0FFDCFCBEFB1913B5C55D" pageId="7" pageNumber="704" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFD0FFDCFCBEFB19122EC7F4" blockId="7.[886,1381,1174,1196]" box="[886,1381,1174,1196]" pageId="7" pageNumber="704">
<heading id="D08281EBFFD0FFDCFCBEFB19122EC7F4" box="[886,1381,1174,1196]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="7" pageNumber="704" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD0FFDCFCBEFB19122EC7F4" authority="(WILLISTON, 1891)" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[886,1381,1174,1196]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="704" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD0FFDCFCBEFB1913C8C7F2" box="[886,1155,1175,1196]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="704">COPESTYLUM ORNATUM</emphasis>
(WILLISTON, 1891)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFD0FFDCFCF2FB3013B5C55D" blockId="7.[826,1441,1213,1541]" pageId="7" pageNumber="704">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD0FFDCFCF2FB3014FEC78B" box="[826,949,1214,1235]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="704">Puparium:</emphasis>
(prothoracic plate missing), largest species of the group, puparium length 
<quantity id="4C8D9B62FFD0FFDCFB7EFB5213B1C7A9" box="[1206,1274,1244,1265]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="704" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
. Anterior fold without extra large spicules. Thorax with lateral fold bearing sensilla 4 of mesothorax wider than band immediately below bearing sensilla 5. Abdominal vestiture of short, upright setae. Anal lobe without spicules. Posterior breathing tube orange, tapering. AP punctured and shiny, and as long as TR is wide. Pupal spiracles dark orange, matt, shining apically, and with openings in upper third. Pupal spiracles 1.1¥ as wide apart as a pupal spiracle is long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36F650CFFD0FFD3FCF2F9C8162CC2CB" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="705" pageId="7" pageNumber="704" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFD0FFDCFCF2F9C8143FC437" blockId="7.[826,1441,1605,1903]" pageId="7" pageNumber="704">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD0FFDCFCF2F9C8124AC503" box="[826,1281,1605,1627]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="704">
Taxonomic notes: 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD0FFDCFBC6F9CB124AC503" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[1038,1281,1605,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="704" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatum">Copestylum ornatum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is similar to those species of the Pictum group having a tapering posterior breathing tube. It can be separated from these species by its large size (puparium length 
<quantity id="4C8D9B62FFD0FFDCFCF2F94E1435C58D" box="[826,894,1728,1749]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="704" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
), upper thoracic lateral fold being wider than the fold immediately below and having dark orange pupal spiracles. In having dark orange pupal spiracles it is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD0FFDCFBE4F89213E8C469" baseAuthorityName="Curran" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[1068,1187,1820,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="704" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imitans">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD0FFDCFBE4F89213E8C469" box="[1068,1187,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="704">C. imitans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but may be separated from that species by its tapering posterior breathing tube.
</paragraph>
